	<section class="fluid-container newspage-news-items clearfix">
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-new-york">
						Facts on New York Medical Marijuana Legislation
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/e92c4094040680166d5c7398299979e7e49e5492.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">New York passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2014 through Assembly Bill 6357. The law allows qualifying patients to possess a&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">30-day supply&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">of medical marijuana. Cultivation of medical marijuana is not allowed.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-new-york" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-new-mexico">
						Understanding Laws on Medical Cannabis in New Mexico
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/0140cc03e49ed3614203aec15a0dc91cb6b3f862.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">New Mexico passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2007 through Senate Bill 523. The law allows qualifying patients to possess&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">6 ounces of medical marijuana and cultivate 4 mature and 12 immature plants</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-new-mexico" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-new-jersey">
						Medical Marijuana in New Jersey: Laws and Procedures
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/4271faa6a3f34e65214ff135cfae049c82cdd281.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">New Jersey passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2010 through Senate Bill 119. The law allows qualifying patients to possess&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">2 ounces of medical marijuana</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. Cultivation of medical marijuana is not allowed.</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-new-jersey" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-new-hampshire">
						New Hampshire Laws and Information on Medical Cannabis You Need to Know
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/31ccb98a0354d2cb1c8c01f6f17203c69f6ef169.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #70574b;"><a href="https://legiscan.com/NH/text/HB573/id/709869" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://legiscan.com/NH/text/HB573/id/709869</a>New</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> Hampshire passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">2013 through House Bill 573</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. The law allows qualifying patients to possess 2 ounces of medical marijuana. Cultivation of medical marijuana is not allowed.</span></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-new-hampshire" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-nevada">
						Nevada Medical Marijuana Laws and Applying Procedures
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/6d6d683d53f1978b130b85a850780d29889e54bf.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Nevada passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2000 through Ballot Question 9 that received 65% of the vote. The law allows qualifying patients to&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">possess 2.5 ounces&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">of medical marijuana. Patients are allowed to cultivate 12 plants.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-nevada" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-montana">
						Montana Laws on Using Cannabis for Medical Purposes
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/f7131384ca7056f0c995551e0963a2def888fd8b.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Montana passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2004 through Initiative 148 that received&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">62% of the vote</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. The law allows qualifying patients to possess 1 ounce of medical marijuana. Patients are allowed to cultivate 4 mature plants and 12 seedlings.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-montana" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-minnesota">
						Medical Marijuana Laws in Minnesota in Nutshell
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/9245d894e7c025b4af67f866b82a1af7d7af4769.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Minnesota passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2014 by passage of Senate Bill 2470.&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The law allows qualifying patients to possess a 30-day supply of non-smokable medical marijuana</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. Cultivation of medical cannabis is not allowed.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-minnesota" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-michigan">
						Understanding Laws on Medical Cannabis in Michigan
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/1f187b97f551116c7261d55527a11e16b1b474f0.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Michigan passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2008 through Proposition 1 that&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">received 63% of the vote</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. The law allows qualifying patients to possess 2.5 ounces of therapeutic marijuana. Patients are allowed to cultivate 12 plants.</span></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-michigan" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-massachusetts">
						Medical Cannabis in Massachusetts: Laws and Requirements
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/9b86d3f19e51bcf765da120cbbc7b62b5ff1c615.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Massachusetts passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2012 through a Ballot Question that received 63% of the vote. The Massachusetts law allows qualifying patients to possess&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">10 ounces, or a 60-day supply</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;of cannabis for medical use.</span></p>
				</div>

